---

# Model Architecture

### DenseNet / CNN
Used for extracting high-level visual features from chest X-ray images.

### GRU Network
Processes sequential patient vitals and captures temporal dependencies in time-series medical data.

### MLP Network
Handles static clinical features and laboratory records for structured tabular learning.

### Fusion Network
Combines features from all modalities to generate the final disease prediction.

---

# Dataset

This project utilizes multimodal healthcare datasets consisting of:

- Chest X-ray images
- Patient vital signs
- Clinical laboratory records
- Structured patient metadata

The preprocessing pipeline includes:
- Image cleaning and normalization
- Time-series preparation
- Tabular feature engineering
- Dataset fusion and alignment

---

# Results

The multimodal fusion approach improves diagnostic capability by leveraging complementary information from multiple clinical sources.

The system is designed to predict respiratory diseases such as:

- Pneumonia
- Pulmonary Edema
- Pleural Effusion
- Consolidation

using fused image, vitals, and clinical features.

